title: Aretha Franklin - 2015-12-06 - Kennedy Center Honors Carole King
description: RTP Aretha Franklin - the Queen of Soul has passed away... :( Another victim of the horrible disease cancer, like so many of our other loved ones. Although a non-harmful cure (CBD) for many cancers has been discovered over a decade ago, big greedy pharmaceutical companies do not want us to use that or even know about it. They rather make their billions each year with toxic chemotherapy. And thus our loved ones keep on dying... while a cure is available. ================================================================================ Kennedy Center Honors Carole King The John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts Washington, DC - December 6, 2015 - Broadcast on CBS-TV on December 29, 2015 Although the main event centers around Carole King, the only true highlight is the very moving performance by Aretha Franklin at the end. Even tough guy Obama sheds a tear :) Main set 01 joke by President Obama 02 intro by Secretary of State John Kerry 03 scene from "Beautiful: The Carole King Musical" 04 Will You Love Me Tomorrow?/One Fine Day - Janelle Monáe 05 more from "Beautiful: The Carole King Musical" 06 Up On The Roof - James Taylor 07 more from "Beautiful: The Carole King Musical" 08 You've Got A Friend - Sara Bareilles 09 more from "Beautiful: The Carole King Musical" 10 (You Make Me Feel Like) A Natural Woman - Aretha Franklin - sings at the piano! Length: 21:50 Finale 11 finals comments from Stephen Colbert 12 I Feel The Earth Move - All, including R2-D2, C-3PO and a bunch of Stormtroopers groovin' to the beat* - *George Lucas was also an honoree at this ceremony https://imgur.com/a/OBFIRSO >> great screenshots https://imgur.com/a/k2wQm < copyright disclaimer, fair use policy
